<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-22T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-22T09:00:00-05:00" n="4" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d4">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111 A.R.N.C./162: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Burdett</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-22T11:00:00-03:00">January 22, 1941—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received January 22—10:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>43. For the Under Secretary from Fenwick. My telegram No. 42, January 21,
                            3 p.m. Contrary to my expectations the Neutrality Committee <pb facs="0013" n="3" xml:id="pg_3"/> reconsidered the text of the
                            Security Zone Convention and eliminated from article III reference to
                            warships making repairs and obtaining fuel in neutral ports.
                            [Fenwick.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Burdett</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>